item.title: Shitty Youtube Update!!!!
item.dc:creator: TheDragonMask
item.description:
I’ve seen this in IE and Opera 10.5. Commenting and making favorites doesn’t work properly, (The comment box only updates after I put the mouse over the video, and the “save to” box won’t even react to clicks) the rating system is crap now, showing every video except for complete crap as “Most Liked” (Compared to what!? Maybe most people liked it? I don’t know, its all crap now), and the videos don’t even play on Opera 10.5!

It said that I was using an old version of flash, so first I thought it was incompatible with flash 10.1 beta. So I switched to a stable release, and It still didn’t work! I noticed that it actually showed the video before switching to an “Old Flash? Upgrade now!” screen! Is this some kind of power grab to switch everyone on Opera and IE to Google Chrome!? (I checked, my version of Chrome used the original UI)

Thankfully Firefox (at least on the computer I’m writing this on, I’ve used others that have the new UI) has not been affected it seems, but who knows how long that will be. This change is NOT something to idly pass by as “Just an update”! This update doesn’t provide any benefit, all it does is [COLOR=‘DarkRed’]replace a simple star system, with an overly simple binary approach to ratings! It [COLOR=‘DarkRed’]pushes the video description down below the video (so no reading it while watching) completely [COLOR=‘DarkRed’]removes channel pictures from anything but the channel it self, and [COLOR=‘Red’]restricts IE and Opera compatibility, rendering them useless for viewing Youtube!!! >

Read full topic

Alright, so I just got it, a lot of people did. It’s a conflict with your bggmap.bmg file in System32.

Delete System32, which houses the revisionary internet protocol drivers so you can restart the revision process correctly.
